# .trivyignore — Trivy CVE allowlist for Spring Petclinic Microservices
#
# Add CVE IDs here (one per line) to suppress known/accepted vulnerabilities
# from failing the CI pipeline. Entries apply to BOTH CRITICAL and HIGH scans.
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN              # suppress globally
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN pkg:version  # suppress for a specific package version (if supported)
#
# Before adding an entry, document:
#   - WHY it is accepted (no fix available, low exploitability, internal-only)
#   - WHEN to re-evaluate (e.g. when a fix is released upstream)
#   - JIRA ticket reference (PETPLAT-xxx)
#
# Example:
#   # CVE-2023-XXXXX: Unfixed in eclipse-temurin:17 base image as of 2026-04.
#   # Re-evaluate when eclipse-temurin:17 releases a patched layer.
#   # Ref: PETPLAT-999
#   CVE-2023-XXXXX
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Currently no accepted CVEs. Add entries below this line only after review.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
